Hier ist gerade jemand, der meinen Küchenboden repariert. Und ich tu jetzt so, als hätte ich noch einen Job und würde von zu Hause aus arbeiten, während ich an Too Hot to Handle sitze.
If I could just damn well open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling super loudly. Yay.
It feels uncomfortably passive-aggressive to crank my air purifier to the max, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would even be completely okay, even if he wasn't a mask opponent. And do I really need to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he's gone.
At least I finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter five is long, but so damned scary. Oh yeah, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing search and replace for … ➡️ ellipsis symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I stick to my point. Natural language is mostly fragmented, especially when one gets emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, this means he'll be done soon.
He went out to cut something (it sounds like that at least). I secretly checked how far he's gotten. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite neat – mainly changes to the font and very small corrections in direct speech, and I need to make everything a bit more concise. But I really need a break and a cup of tea now, but the kitchen guy is still in my kitchen.
He just started vacuuming again. Hopefully, this is a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he had prepared a cost estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were stingy and only paid for the part next to the door that is no longer in good condition. It feels much better already.
The house is being ventilated and my air purifier is running in the kitchen, while I'm drinking tea in the garden!
